Section 1:
1 L.D. 1785
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Clerk of the House.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1196, L.D. 1785, “An Act to Encourage
10 Competition by Requiring Independent Health Care Provider Cost-of-living Adjustments
11 in Health Insurance Contracts”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Require Health Insurance Carriers to Provide Contact Information for
14 Employees Responsible for Negotiating Health Care Provider Contracts'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 24-A MRSA §4303, sub-§18, ¶B, as enacted by PL 2013, c. 399, §1, is
18 amended to read:
19 B. Upon the provider's request at the time a contract for a preferred provider
20 arrangement is offered, the following must be provided to a provider for review:
21 (1) The fee schedule or, if there is not a fee schedule for one or more of the services
22 covered under the contract, the terms under which payment is determined. A
23 carrier may require a provider to execute a nondisclosure agreement covering the
24 information provided under this subparagraph; and
25 (2) The identity of all carriers for which the provider is agreeing to provide
26 services to health plan enrollees.; and
27 (3) Contact information for the carrier's employee responsible for negotiating all
28 contract terms with the provider, including, but not limited to, the fee schedule.
29 Contact information provided under this subparagraph must include, at a
30 minimum, the position title of the carrier's employee, the employee's telephone
31 number and the employee's e-mail address. A carrier shall update this contact
32 information on the carrier's electronic portal for providers or, if the carrier does not
33 have an electronic portal, by other means of electronic notification to providers.'
34 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
35 number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR2316(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1196, L.D. 1785
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment requires that,
33 upon a health care provider's request, the health insurance carrier provide the health care
44 provider with contact information for the carrier's employee responsible for negotiating
55 contract terms with the provider, including the fee schedule, at the time the contract is
66 offered to the provider. The amendment also requires a carrier to keep this information
77 updated on the carrier's electronic portal for providers or, if the carrier does not have an
88 electronic portal, by other means of electronic notification.
Page 2 - 132LR2316(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
